## Key Engine Architecture
- Vulkan renderer, push constants: mat4 model at offset 0
- UBO SceneData: mat4 view, mat4 proj, vec4 light_dir, vec4 camera_pos
- Vertex3D: float pos[3], normal[3], color[3]
- draw_frame(SceneData, Mesh* entity, vector<ParticleVertex>*, vector<uint32_t>*, float total_time)
- Entity buffers: entity_vb_, entity_ib_, upload_entity_mesh() - uploads each frame
- Pipeline: pipeline_ (opaque), particle_pipeline_ (additive)
- Camera: forward(), right(), yaw, pitch, fov, view_matrix(), projection_matrix(aspect)
- Level loader: load_level_gltf(path) -> LevelData { Mesh mesh; vector<HMM_Vec3> spawn_points; }
- Action enum in keybinds.h: MoveForward,MoveBack,MoveRight,MoveLeft,Jump,Crouch - need Shoot,Reload,ADS
- Main.cpp: shooting at line ~454, entity_mesh at line ~551, draw_frame at line ~871
- Renderer: depth_format_ = VK_FORMAT_D32_SFLOAT, depth_image_, depth_view_, depth_memory_
- Render pass: attachment[0]=color, attachment[1]=depth

## Viewmodel Rendering Strategy
1. After entities, clear depth only (vkCmdClearAttachments depth)
2. Draw viewmodel with same pipeline_ but custom projection (near=0.01)
3. Viewmodel buffers: viewmodel_vb_, viewmodel_ib_ (same pattern as entity)
4. upload_viewmodel_mesh() method
5. Model matrix = camera-relative (hip_offset lerped to ads_offset)

